1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,840
In 1950, the physicist Enrico Fermi was having lunch, chatting about aliens when he asked

2
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:07,760
one question that has haunted science ever since.

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:09,240
Where is everybody?

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:12,200
The galaxy is huge and billions of years old.

5
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:15,320
If life is common, somebody should have shown up by now.

6
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:17,240
The simplest answer is also the most humbling.
